<HEADLINE> Victims Friendly Courts Proving Effective in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Victims Friendly Courts (VFC)
 introduced in Zimbabwe six years ago have proven an effective
method in dealing with problems faced by vulnerable groups when
their cases came up for trial.
</P>
<P>
VFC National Chairman David Mangota Monday told the Zimbabwe
News Agency that changes in investigation and social welfare
intervention had contributed a lot to the success of the system.
</P>
<P>
"The multi-sectoral cooperation has made it so easy for
officers to cope with changes which have made the court system
accessible to children," said Mangota.
</P>
<P>
He said non-governmental organizations were instrumental in
providing expertise to officers directly involved in the process.
</P>
<P>
Advantages associated with the system were that children no
longer faced the accused in court and suffered no trauma from
harsh cross examination, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
