<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 11 in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed
and eight others injured in a traffic accident Monday morning in
North Tanzania's Arusha Region, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
A vehicle was carrying about 27 people to attend a funeral but
overturned some eight kilometers from the Arusha town.
</P>
<P>
The victims included the driver and a pregnant woman. The
injured had been rushed to a nearby hospital with four in critical
condition, most of them suffered head, chest and spinal injuries,
the reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
