<HEADLINE> U.S. Soccer Federation Denies Contacts with Iraqis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Soccer Federation on
Monday denied any contacts with the Iraqi federation and any
arrangement for any charity matches with the Iraqi national soccer
team in the United States.
</P>
<P>
"We have not made any contact with Iraq and have no plans to
play them. The U.S. Soccer Federation also has no plans to make
any contacts with Iraq," Jim Moorhouse, spokesman for the U.S.
Soccer Federation in Chicago, said.
</P>
<P>
He was commenting a report that Iraq and American sports
authorities have agreed to stage a string of charity soccer
friendlies in the United States later this year.
</P>
<P>
The report was made by the Iraqi agency, which quoted a
spokesman for the Iraqi National Olympic Committee as saying
final dates for the matches between the national Iraqi team and
U.S. sides were being fixed. 
</P>
