<HEADLINE> Leader Stresses Importance of Military Modernization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A leader of the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) Monday stressed the importance of military
modernization, but reiterated that the country will find a
peaceful solution to the dispute with Iran over the three Gulf
islands.
</P>
<P>
"The strategic position occupied by the UAE and the changes
taking place in the region and around the world have prompted the
country to modernize its armed forces and enhance their level of
preparedness," said Abu Dhabi Crown Prince Sheikh Khalifa Bin
Zayed Al Nahyan.
</P>
<P>
Khalifa, the deputy supreme commander of the UAE armed forces,
made the remarks on the occasion of the graduation of a group of
students from the Command and Staff College, the Emirates News
Agency (WAM) reported.
</P>
<P>
"The armed forces have to be equipped with the latest
technology to enable them to face the challenges of the 21st
century and to protect the country and its achievements for
future generations," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he reiterated the UAE's position of finding a
peaceful solution to the dispute with Iran over the Gulf islands
of Abu Musa and Greater and Lesser Tunbs.
</P>
<P>
The three islands, which are located near strategic shipping
lanes in the Gulf, are claimed by both countries, but controlled
by Iran.
</P>
<P>
The UAE accuses Iran of not responding actively to its calls
for dialogs on the dispute.
</P>
<P>
The dispute should be solved "either through serious bilateral
talks or by referring the issue to the International Court of
Justice and we declare in advance that we will abide by the
decision of the court," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that resolving the issue of the islands would
contribute to the strengthening of peace and security in the
region and pave the way for the establishing of security,
economic and political cooperation in the Gulf region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
