<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola Needs to Import Grain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Food crisis in the forthcoming
commercial year 1999/2000 will make it necessary for Angola to
import 505,000 tons of grain, Angolan Minister of Agriculture and
Rural Development said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Of this amount, 325,000 tons will depend on commercial import
while the rest 180,000 tons will be covered by food assistance,
said agriculture minister Gilberto Lutukuta.
</P>
<P>
According to Lutukuta, Angola's domestic grain output in 1999
will be 562,000 tons, down 5.4 percent, or 32,000 tons, from the
output in 1998.
</P>
<P>
He said that due to the sharp decline in the petroleum price,
the economic situation in Angola considerably aggravated in the
commercial year 1998.
</P>
<P>
He also attributed the drop of grain production to the endless
civil war, which has caused serious economic problems in recent
years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
