<HEADLINE> Dismissed Miners Back at Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The 9,000 miners dismissed
Friday were reinstated and back at work Monday, said
Secretary-General of the National Union of Mine workers (NUM)
Gwede Mantashe.
</P>
<P>
The workers were dismissed from Durban Roodeport Deep's
Hartebeesfontein mine when they challenged the conditions of sale
of the mine from Avgold to Durban Roodepoort Deep (DRD).
</P>
<P>
Mantashe told the press that they would not only retain the
conditions of employment they had with Avgold, but would receive a
nine-percent across- the-board salary increase, backdated to July
1.
</P>
<P>
NUM had finally agreed on increasing annual wages for the three
other DRD mines, -- Buffelsfontein, Blyvooruitzicht and Durban
Roodepoort Deep itself, he said.
</P>
<P>
Both parties agreed to engage in relationship and team building
to improve mutual trust and communication, and to discuss
strategic issues regularly.
</P>
<P>
DRD chief executive Mike Prinsloo said the agreement
represented a fresh spirit of constructive co-operation and
augured well for the future of Harties and all its people.
</P>
