 Zimbabwean economy well into the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture directly and indirectly provides more than 50
percent of total employment in the country, while contributing
over 15 percent of the Gross Domestic Product.
</P>
<P>
It generates some 40 percent of the country's foreign exchange
earnings and provides most of the raw materials to the
manufacturing sector. 
