<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Chinese President Meets With Special Libyan Envoy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting with Omar Mustafa Al-Muntasser, a special envoy of Libyan
leader Muammar Qaddafi here this evening in the Great Hall of the
People, said that African countries are important developing
countries and an important force for establishing a new
international political and economic order that is just and fair.
</P>
<P>
Muntasser is the secretary of the People's General Committee
for Foreign Liaison and International Cooperation of Libya and is
here to deliver a letter from Qaddafi. He discussed the recent
35th summit meeting of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) in
Algeria with Jiang and the coming special OAU summit to be held in
Libya.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the African situation is mainly one of seeking
peace, stability and development and that African countries and
regional organizations on the continent have made an effort to
safeguard regional peace and stability and to resolve the
differences between or within some countries, and tangible results
can be seen.
</P>
<P>
He particularly mentioned the strong call for unity by African
countries for greater strength in regional cooperation and
economic development after the 35th OAU summit and said that he
wishes the OAU special summit success.
</P>
