<HEADLINE> Seoul Stock Index Surges 4.46 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Korea Composite Stock Price
Index soared 4.46 percent to 917.58 points on Monday, as foreign
and institution investors poured in huge amounts of capital into
the market.
</P>
<P>
The 39.19 point jump from the previous trading day was
significant as the index has seen only slight increases in the
past few days.
</P>
<P>
Stock analysts attributed the big index rise to a possible
upgrading of South Korea's sovereign credit rating by Moody's
Investor Service.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, some 84 financial institutions had promised
to help stabilize the ailing financial market by refraining from
taking their investments out of bond funds, according to the
Financial Supervisory Commission.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the South Korean currency devalued by 3.60 won
against the U.S. dollar, closing at 1197.20. 
</P>
