<HEADLINE> Schroeder Inaugurates New Office in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, August 23 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder opened his new office here Monday afternoon in the
country's new center of power, marking the accomplishment of
another major task in the monumental "Bonn-to-Berlin" trek.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inauguration ceremony, Schroeder said, "This
is a historic moment." He thanked both Bonn and Berlin, as well as
many historical events and people that made the day possible.
</P>
<P>
He said that Berlin will face great challenges and he was
certain that it would become "one of the great metropolises of the
world."
</P>
<P>
Schroeder started work in his temporary quarters that used to
be former East German leaders' office, where he will work until
the new chancellery is completed next year.
</P>
<P>
Joschka Fischer, vice-chancellor and minister of Foreign
Affairs, moved into his office in Berlin at mid-day.
</P>
<P>
The German parliament is scheduled to hold the first plenary
meeting at the Reichstag in Berlin on September 6, making the
start of full-fledged operations. From that day on, all
government authorities and the parliament will start work in the
new capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
