<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Further Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The average crude oil price
continued rising this week to 19.92 U.S. dollars per barrel, 33
cents more than that of last week, according to figures released
by the Vienna-based Secretariat of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries (OPEC) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The price had fallen to only 9.5 dollars per barrel in February,
but eventually rose to 18.28 dollars per barrel in July.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the price hike to OPEC members sticking to
the agreement reached in March of reducing oil production to
protect the price.
</P>
<P>
The reduction of crude oil mining in the North Sea and the
decrease of Russia's oil exports resulting from its own increasing
demand are also factors lowering oil storage and pushing the price
up, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
