<HEADLINE> Greek Equity Prices Hit New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Greek equity prices hit new
records Monday with the general index on the Athens Stock Exchange
(ASE) breaking the 5,000 level for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The ASE general index ended 2.56 percent higher at 5,066.39
points, its 42nd record since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index also rose 2.17 percent to 2,752.02
points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 305.5 billion drachmas (about 1 billion U.S.
dollars), and advancers led decliners by 243 to 50 with another
four issues unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The construction and leasing sectors led the rising stock
market, ending 6.85 percent and 6.34 percent higher respectively.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts expected the market to find its next resistance
level at 5,250 points. 
