<HEADLINE> Highlight of Diplomatic News Today (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The following is the highlight
of diplomatic news released by Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Meets UPU Officials
</P>
<P>
As the Universal Postal Union (UPU) stages its first ever
congress in China, President Jiang Zemin today declared that China
will continue to strengthen cooperation with various countries in
the postal field.
</P>
<P>
The UPU congress begins here today and will conclude on
September 15. More than 2,200 representatives from over 180
countries and 30-plus international organizations are
participating.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Meets With Special Libyan Envoy
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting with Omar Mustafa Al-
Muntasser, a special envoy of Libyan leader Muammar Qaddafi here
this evening in the Great Hall of the People, said that African
countries are important developing countries and an important
force for establishing a new international political and economic
order that is just and fair.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese President Meets with Sultan of Brunei
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting today with Hassanal Bolkiah,
the Sultan and head of state of Brunei, said that China considers
cooperation with Brunei very important and that he wishes to push
bilateral relations with Brunei forward to a new stage.
</P>
<P>
China, Brunei Issue Joint Communique
</P>
<P>
China and Brunei today issued a joint communique after
presidential talks, agreeing to further develop the relations of
good neighborliness, friendship and cooperation based on mutual
trust and support between the two countries taking into account
the 1997 Joint Statement of the Meeting of the Leaders of China
and ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Meets Egyptian Military Officials
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Chi Haotian believes that the current visit by
Egyptian Commander of Air Defense Mohammed Abdel Hamid El Shehat
will push bilateral cooperation in air defense to a new level.
</P>
<P>
While meeting the Egyptian guests, Chi, also vice-chairman of
the Central Military Commission (CMC) and a state councilor, said
today that China and Egypt, as developing countries, share
extensive common interests and have broad prospects for friendly
cooperation.
</P>
</TEXT>
