</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Chi Haotian exchanged views on the situation
in Northeast Asia here today with Republic of Korea (ROK)
counterpart Cho Sung-Tae, the first ROK Defense Minister to visit
China since the two countries forged diplomatic ties in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
a state councilor, reiterated China's stand toward the Korean
Peninsula issue, and said that "China sincerely hopes that the
situation there will ease and the peninsula will be a nuclear-free
region and finally realize a lasting peace and stability."
</P>
