<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0058 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Able to Stabilize Currency: Central Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 23 (Xinhua)-- Tanzania's central bank
said Monday that the country has enough foreign reserves to
stabilize its currency shilling.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Tanzania said in a statement that its gross foreign
 exchange reserves are at a record high of 587 million U.S.
dollars, equivalent to more than four months merchandised imports.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the commercial banks hold another 372 million
dollars, the central Bank Governor Daudi Ballali said in the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate between the Tanzania shilling and the U.S.
dollar was pegged at 800:1 at the end of July, broadly in line
with economic fundamentals, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania currency depreciated some 10 percent from June to July
this year, which caused alarm among traders.
</P>
<P>
The central bank explained that a drop in exports by 30 percent
in the past two years was the main factor behind the depreciation.
</P>
<P>
The continued growth in imports, in the face of failing
exports, was an added factor in the depreciation of Tanzania
shilling, the bank said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
