<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Namibia to Lift State of Emergency in Caprivi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The state of emergency
imposed on Namibia's remote Caprivi Strip after a rebel uprising
would end Wednesday, South African media reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The situation has stabilized and it is no longer necessary to
have the state of emergency in the Caprivi. But our forces will
continue patrolling the region as a normal practice," Namibian
Defense Force Chief of Staff, Major General Martin Shalli, was
quoted as saying Monday.
</P>
<P>
Namibian President Sam Nujoma declared a state of emergency in
the region after an armed incursion by secessionist rebels who
attacked Katima Mulilo, a major town in the region on August 2.
</P>
</TEXT>
