<HEADLINE> Tanzania Blasts Child Labor in Flower Farms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government
Monday blasted child labor in flower farms and called for the
setting up of health committees in the flower industry.
</P>
<P>
Opening a two-day workshop of the flower industry's impact on
economy and community in the northern town of Arusha, Minister of
Labor and Youth Paul Kimiti said that child labor is not allowed
in the industry.
</P>
<P>
He also called for support to small-scale flower farms,
underlining that they can work alongside with big farms and
benefit from modern technology and science.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from the International Labor Organization attended
the workshop. 
</P>
