<HEADLINE> London Stock Market Surges To Month High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A surge in Wall Street helped
London's FTSE-100 Index closed up 141.3 points at 6322.1 Monday,
that swept the index to its highest close in a month.
</P>
<P>
The gains followed a strong opening on Wall Street with the Dow
Jones Industrial Average putting on triple digit gains during the
session, building on Friday's 137-point rise.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector, which accounts for around 18 percent of the
FTSE 100's market capitalisation, helped propel the index to its
highs.
</P>
<P>
HSBC share price advanced 32p to 797p, while Lloyds TSB climbed
45p to 899p and Bank of Scotland 47-1/2p to 786-1/2p.
</P>
<P>
The German Dax rallied, helped by talk of a major banking
merger and the easing of fears of major increases in interest
rates in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The electronic Xetra Dax sprinted 0.91 percent higher to
finished at 5301.98.
</P>
<P>
Deutsche Bank and Dresdner, two of the biggest banks in
Germany, confirmed that they were in talks about combining their
retail operations.
</P>
<P>
Shares in Deutsche Bank and Dresdner Bank surged on the news.
Dresdner Bank was up 4.2 percent at 44.89 euro and Deutsche Bank
was up 5.2 percent at 66.99 euro.
</P>
<P>
Paris' Cac 40 index of leading shares ended up 15 points at
4487, after briefly breaking through the 4500 level earlier in the
session.  
</P>
</TEXT>
