<HEADLINE> Thailand's Exports Rise 0.8 percent in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's export in the first
half of this year were valued at 27.1 billion U.S. dollars, an
increase of 0.8 percent over the same period last year, the Thai
government said in a press release issued on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The best performers in export were industrial and
agro-industrial products which increased 5.8 percent and 3.1
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the export increase to the economic
recovery trend in Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's total imports from January to June rose by 8.5
percent to 23.2 billion dollars. As a result, the country
registered a trade surplus of 3.9 billion dollars, down 29.7
percent from the same period last year. 
</P>
