<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Industrial Production Gains Slight Strength </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Industrial production in both
the European Union and the euro zone witnessed a modest upward
trend in the months from April to June, Eurostat reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the European
community said that industrial production rose by 0.4 percent in
the 15-nation European Union and 0.3 percent in the 11-nation euro
zone.
</P>
<P>
The industrial production in the previous three months grew by
0.2 percent for both the union and the zone of the single currency.
</P>
<P>
Finland recorded a 1.1 percent increase in industrial
production, the biggest of all EU member states, followed by
Portugal with 0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Production of durable consumer goods was up 0.5 percent for
both the union and euro zone while that of capital goods declined
by 0.2 percent in the euro zone and was up 0.1 percent for the
European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
