<HEADLINE> Russia Slams Kosovo Albanians' Provocation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Russia said Tuesday that Kosovo
Albanians' attempt to block Russian peacekeepers entering Orahovac
in Kosovo was "a well-organized provocation planned in advance."
</P>
<P>
Such a provocation represents "an open challenge to the
international community and directly contradicts Resolution 1244
of the U.N. Security Council," the Russian Foreign Ministry said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
These actions have breached "the Kosovo settlement principles,
which were adopted by the G8 countries and the coordinated
Helsinki agreement detailing Russia's participation in the
international force and the two protocols to it," the statement
said. 
