<HEADLINE> Luxembourg Offers Aid to Turkish Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Luxembourg on Tuesday offered a
humanitarian aid of 50 million francs (1.3 million U.S. dollars)
to Turkish earthquake victims.
</P>
<P>
A government statement said that Luxembourg had rented a
Belgian military transport plane to send to Turkey on Tuesday
urgent humanitarian materials such as tents, plastic gloves and
mortuary bags to Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The materials were worth 5 million francs while the remainder
of the humanitarian aid would be spent on supporting international
rescue efforts by the Red Cross, the UNICEF and other
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake on August 17 in northwestern Turkey has claimed
an official toll of 14,360 people and left 200,000 others homeless.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has appealed for foreign assistance as torrential rains
hampered rescue efforts. Tent camps sheltering quake survivors
have turned into mud land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
