<HEADLINE> Chinese And Mauritian FMs Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan,
in talks with his Mauritian counterpart Rajkeswur Purryag here
today, said that China will work with Mauritius to seek new
approaches and new means of bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Tang says he values the friendship and cooperative ties between
the two countries, which were established on the basis of the Five
Principles of Peaceful Coexistence and that Sino-Mauritian
relations have gone smoothly and healthily since diplomatic ties
were forged 27 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Friendships between people are deepening and bilateral
cooperation in politics, the economy, and culture are bearing
fruit, and the two countries share a consensus on some major
international issues, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his pleasure at the successful exchange of visits
by the leaders of the two countries, which have enhanced bilateral
relations and said he appreciates Mauritius' adherence to the "One
China" policy and its support for China's reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
All countries are equal members of the international community
regardless of their size, strength, or wealth, and the Chinese
government places importance on its ties with Mauritius and hopes
to bring better Sino-Mauritian relations to the 21st century, he
said.
</P>
