<HEADLINE> Indian Protests Against Bangladesh over Border Firing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- India Tuesday lodged a protest
with Bangladesh over the firing by Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) at
Border Security Force (BSF) personnel at Muhirirchar, a border
area which India said in South Tripura district of West Bengal
state.
</P>
<P>
The Acting High Commissioner of Bangladesh Alimul Haque was
summoned to the Foreign Office and asked to convey to his
government the need for an early end to the firing and for a flag
meeting between the local commanders of the BSF and BDR in order
to defuse the situation.
</P>
<P>
An External Affairs Ministry spokesperson said that the firing
stopped Tuesday at 1400 local time and a flag meeting is scheduled
to take place Wednesday at 0930 local time.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Indian government is monitoring the situation
closely.
</P>
<P>
The problem arose due to local differences over cultivation
across the riverine boundary, official sources said. 
