<HEADLINE> Elf Chief Says Balance of Force Changes in Wrestling With Total </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Officer of Elf-
Aquitaine oil group, Philippe Jaffre, said on Tuesday that the
balance of force in his arms wrestling with his rival, Franco-
Belgian oil group Total-Fina, is in the process of changing.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the newspaper Le Monde, Jaffre said that a
solution to the merger battle between the two oil and chemical
giants can be found if the president of Total-Fina, Thierry
Desmarest, confirms his intention to seek a solution.
</P>
<P>
Elf made a furious counter acquisition bid against Total-Fina a
month ago in reaction to a surprise bid on it by the latter on
July 5.
</P>
<P>
Since then, both Elf and Total-Fina have been seeking a
compromise version of an apparently inevitable merger, which will
result in the world's fourth largest oil and gas group and the
fifth biggest chemicals group.
</P>
<P>
The French government, which has the final power of arbitration
or veto over the merger, has maintained neutrality but seems to
encourage the merger move.
</P>
<P>
Jaffre criticized Total-Fina for seeking a merger with Elf "
within two months." 
</P>
</TEXT>
