<HEADLINE> China Ready to Promote Ties with Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- China values relations with
Sierra Leone and its parliament that have gone smoothly since the
establishment of diplomatic ties 28 years ago, said Li Peng,
chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting here today with Sheku Mohammed Fadril Kutubu,
speaker of the House of Representatives of Sierra Leone, Li said
that the two developing countries have supported and cooperated
with each other in international affairs, while the two
parliaments have maintained fine relations.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his belief that the visit will promote the
friendship and cooperative ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li emphasized China's appreciation for Sierra Leone's adhering
to the "one China" policy and not developing official ties with
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
China is delighted to see that the Sierra Leonean government
and people are now actively engaged in restoring peace and
reconstructing the economy, thanks to support from the
international community and the leadership of President Tejan
Kabbah.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to push the international community to
support the peace process in Sierra Leone and hopes that Sierra
Leone will make new progress in an overall peace and rebuilding
homes, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Kutubu said that there are no problems between Sierra Leone and
China. Sierra Leone considers China a sincere friend and will
never change its policy of developing friendly relations with
China, he said, adding that the Sierra Leonean parliament will
willing to increase ties with the NPC.  
</P>
