<HEADLINE> Gold, Silver Prices Decline Sharply in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Gold and silver prices showed
a sharp decline on the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay) Tuesday
due to the steep fall of prices in the global market.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that the gold prices came down to touch a
three-week low on the New York market and extended the weakness in
Asian markets where traders indulged in panic selling.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold moved down by 30 rupees (0.70 U.S. dollar) to
finish at 4,070 rupees (94.65 dollars) per ten gram from 4,100
rupees (95.35 dollars) recorded Monday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, silver ready spot (.999 fineness) fell sharply by
100 rupees (2.32 dollars) to close at 8,050 rupees (187.21
dollars) per kilogram from Monday's close of 8,150 rupees (189.53
dollars). 
</P>
