<HEADLINE> Chinese, Georgian Defense Ministers Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian, in a meeting here today with his Georgian counterpart
David Tevzadze, said that Tevzadze's China visit is an important
event in military exchanges between the two countries and will lay
a good foundation for further friendly cooperation by the two
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
There are many new developments in global multipolarization in
both political and economic arenas after the Cold War and the
trend toward multipolarization will benefit world peace, stability,
and prosperity, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
Under new international circumstances, he said, China is
pursuing an independent foreign policy of peace and is willing to
make a concerted effort with other countries to push for a
peaceful, stable, and prosperous world in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Tevzadze said that China is a great nation and the military
cooperation between Georgia and China is significant and has a
great many prospects. China had made great achievements in the
past 50 years and Georgia could learn from China, he added.
</P>
<P>
Tevzadze is in China at Chi's invitation. Before the meeting,
Chi held a welcoming ceremony for the Georgian guest.  
</P>
</TEXT>
