<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Injured in Slum Explosion in Bangladeshi Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Four people were critically
injured in an explosion in a slum in the Bangladeshi capital city
Dhaka Tuesday afternoon, the BSS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A group of "terrorists" were manufacturing bombs in a house in
a slum to resist a possible eviction drive, police were quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Four of them suffered critical sprinter injuries when some
bombs exploded suddenly. Three were admitted to Dhaka Medical
College Hospital, and the other was taken to the Orthopedics
Hospital under police guard.
</P>
<P>
The "terrorists" were arrested and some bombs-manufacturing
materials were recovered from the spot, the BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The government evicted some 70,000 slum dwellers from the city
early this month following the killing a police constable, on the
ground that the slums had become dens of terrorists and criminals.
</P>
<P>
It is said that about 2 million slum dwellers are living in
Dhaka, which has a population of about 9 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
