<HEADLINE> People's Daily Says Falun Gong Practitioners Should Be United (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The fight against Li Hongzhi and his Falun Gong has had
remarkable successes, it says, and most Falun Gong practitioners
have seen the truth about Falun Gong cult and broken with it.
Party members, officials and working people have been educated,
the country has maintained stability, society has more interest in
science and technology, and the reforms and opening up are
progressing, it says.
</P>
<P>
The Central Committee of the Communist Party's decision to ban
Falun Gong was in the fundamental interest of the entire nation
and was timely and necessary, it says, and the major task facing
Party and government departments now is to continue educating
Falun Gong practitioners who practiced Falun Gong simply to
benefit their health and who knew nothing about Li's political
ambitions.
</P>
<P>
When presented with the facts, the majority of them got a clear
idea about Li and his cult and repented and have done well in
exposing Li and his organization, it says, and those who have
broken with Falun Gong should be helped zealously and no prejudice
should be shown them.
</P>
