<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councilor Meets UNFPA Director </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor Wang
Zhongyu met today with Nafis Sadik, executive director of the
United Nations Population Fund (UNFPA).
</P>
<P>
Wang, also secretary-general of the State Council, and Sadik
exchanged views on issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Population Fund, established in 1969, is the
largest international organization providing assistance to
developing countries in the area of population.
</P>
<P>
It has had fruitful cooperation with China in areas of genital
health, family planning, poverty relief, women's participation in
development and population studies since the signing of a memo of
understanding in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the projects implemented by the United Nations
Population Fund in China have also yielded good economic and
social results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
