<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agricultural Bank Issues Industrial Credit List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China (
ABC) today released a list of industries that qualify for bank
credit.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said that it is meant to promote the
implementation of the state's industrial policies and adjust
credit to reduce risks. It lists industries that should be
supported, restricted, or shut down to keep in line with state
policies.
</P>
<P>
It describes some 1,000 products and projects in more than 30
industries, which include agriculture, forestry, water
conservation, transportation, postal service, telecommunications,
iron and steel, chemicals, construction materials, medicines,
machinery, and electronics.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the bank will give strong support to
industries and projects that are encouraged by the state's
policies and stop loans to industries that have been banned.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
