<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Dominican President of Senate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Even though China and Dominica
have not yet established diplomatic ties, the current visit by
President of the Dominican Senate Ramon Alburquerque will help
increase mutual understanding and friendship, and lay foundation
for future cooperation in various fields, said Li Peng, chairman
of the Chinese National People's Congress Standing Committee, here
today.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting with Alburquerque this afternoon, Li said
that the two countries, though geographically far apart, both
belong to developing countries and support each other in their
fight for national independence.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people cherish friendly feelings for the Dominican
and both parliaments have carried out exchanges," said Li.
</P>
<P>
Alburquerque hailed China's great achievement in its reform and
economic construction, adding that Dominica hopes to enhance
economic and trade ties, as well as civil exchanges, with China.
</P>
<P>
He also voiced the hope that both parliaments improve their
ties so as to push forward the equal and mutual-benefit
relationship between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
