<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Rural Areas Undergoing Historic Changes (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A report from Ministry of
Agriculture indicates that China's grain output this year is
expected to near 500 million tons, basically equaling last year.
</P>
<P>
This will be the fifth consecutive bumper grain harvest China
has enjoyed since 1995.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, the per capita share of grain, meat, eggs and milk
of Chinese people has exceeded or neared the world average,
meaning that China has basically solved the food problem which has
affected it for hundreds of years.
</P>
<P>
The per capita share of grain, meat, eggs and milk of Chinese
people is, respectively, over 400 kilograms, 50 kilometers, 17
kilometers and 6.6 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 50 years, China has increased its annual grain
production capacity from the initial 100 million tons to about 500
million tons while reducing the number of the impoverished
population to 42 million last year from 250 million in 1978.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, farmers' income has surged, accompanied by a
remarkable improvement in the quality of life and living
environment, which has laid a solid foundation for the nation's
economic development and social stability.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics from the National bureau of
Statistics, the average annual net income of farmers soared to 2,
162 yuan in 1998 from 44 yuan in 1949.
</P>
<P>
And in the past 20 years, their income reported a 16-fold
increase, thanks to the reform and opening up policies introduced
in 1978.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicated that farmers' spending on food accounted
for 69 percent of the total when new China was founded in 1949,
but the figure dropped to 53 percent by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
However, their spending on education, recreation and services
grew to 10 percent, with the livable housing space rising to 23.7
square meters per capita.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
