<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Capital Goods Market Remains Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- China's capital goods market has
been developing smoothly since July this year, with prices of most
steel products declining, and sales of automobiles improving,
according to the State Administration of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
As demand for investment in infrastructure projects cooled down,
the prices of most steel products dropped on average by two
percent in July, although the price of steel plates remained
strong.
</P>
<P>
However, experts pointed out that the prices of steel products
will rebound in the later half of this year as a result of the
government's active financial policies.
</P>
<P>
The prices of major nonferrous metal products are expected to
remain stable, and the trend will continue in August and September
this year, according to statistics released by the administration'
s Materials Information Center.
</P>
<P>
Chemical products did not sell well but sales of automobiles,
mostly sedan cars, mini-bus and automobiles for both passenger and
cargo uses, increased by a small margin.
</P>
<P>
In July, the average price of 22 types of automobiles rose a
little from that of the previous month, the center said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
