<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Encourages Local Enterprises to Develop Overseas Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is taking measures to
encourage local manufacturing and processing businesses to do
business and sell their products to foreign countries, the city's
Deputy Mayor Zhang Mao said today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that priority will be given to developing potential
markets in countries and regions such as Africa, Asia, South
America, East Europe, and the Commonwealth of Independent States.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Beijing municipal government plans to
establish an Internet business site which will provide information
on overseas trade opportunities to local enterprises. The city
will also assist these firms with loans, financial aid, trade
quotas and personnel training programs.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Beijing municipal government has given approval for
local enterprises to open more than 280 branches in 60 countries
and regions. The Chinese have invested a total of 200 million US
dollars in the effort.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas branches of Beijing-based enterprises
has reached 150, and most of them are turning a profit.
</P>
<P>
China's total investment in foreign countries has reached 6.3
billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
