<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cruise Liner and Cargo Ship Collide off UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Three people were injured when a
cruise liner with some 2,400 passengers on board collided with a
container vessel off England's southeast coast on early Tuesday,
British coastguards said.
</P>
<P>
Two helicopters airlifted the three injured from the Bahamas-
registered Norwegian Dream cruise ship to hospital in England.
</P>
<P>
The injuries were minor, the Reuters news agency quoted a
spokesman for coastguards in the English port of Dover as saying.
</P>
<P>
The cruise liner later limped into Dover after the collision
which also left the container ship ablaze.
</P>
<P>
Three containers were tipped onto the cruiser when the ships
collided, and others went into the sea.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegian Dream's bridge was badly damaged and its bow
dented.
</P>
<P>
The 17 crew on the Panama-registered container vessel Ever
Decent were battling to contain a cargo fire.
</P>
<P>
Helicopters, tugs, lifeboats and the German frigate Augsburg
raced to help the Ever Decent shortly after the accident in the
Channel -- one of the world's busiest shipping lanes.
</P>
<P>
A British Royal Air Force Nimrod aircraft was monitoring the
situation and five merchant ships were ready to assist.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said there were no details on how the collision
occurred. He dismissed as "speculative" reports that the
container ship was already on fire when it collided with the
Norwegian Dream. 
</P>
</TEXT>
