<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Friendship Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji today
expressed his satisfaction with the vigorous development of Sino-
Russian ties during his meeting with visiting Russian Vice Prime
Minister Ilya Klebanov.
</P>
<P>
"Bilateral relations have maintained a healthy development
trend," Zhu said, adding that the Sino-Russian cooperative
strategic partnership initiated by both President Jiang Zemin and
President Boris Yeltsin is in the fundamental interests of the
people of the two countries and have earned their support.
</P>
<P>
Zhu cited the partnership as trans-century cooperation which
will benefit both countries and help maintain peace and stability
in the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Klebanov said that both Russia and China advocate multi-
polarization and that Russia hopes there will be no deviation from
the right track of the multi-polarization process.
</P>
<P>
"The two countries should further their bilateral friendship,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
The Russian visitor is here at the invitation of Zhang Wannian,
vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
