<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Biggest Beer Brewery Reclaims Trademark in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Tsingtao Brewery, China's
biggest beer brewery, has successfully reclaimed its trademark of
Tsingtao Beer in Hong Kong, according to a senior official for the
company.
</P>
<P>
Li Guirong, chairman of the Tsingtao Brewery Co. Ltd., Tuesday
told a press conference at Furama Hotel here that the company has
achieved prominent interim results for the first half of 1999.
</P>
<P>
"The company's turnover totaled 1.13 billion RMB yuan (136
million U.S. dollars) in the first six months this year, with an
increase of 43 percent compared with the same period of last year,
" Li said.
</P>
<P>
Facing the stagnant demand and weak consumption in the first
half of this year, it achieved an output of 446,000 tons of beer,
a growth of 89 percent, making it the largest brewery in China in
terms of scale and market share, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li attributed the company's fast growth in production and sales
to a large distribution network of 42 agencies throughout the
country and streamlining of the company's management.
</P>
<P>
In the second half of the year, Li said that his company will
continue to increase investment and promote the merger and
acquisition of breweries in China.
</P>
<P>
Among the business strategies, the company will put Shenzhen
Tsingtao Asahi into operation to expand the southern China market.
Efforts will be made to expand its world-wide sales network and to
achieve an annual beer production of one million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
