<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK to Conduct Study on Transport Information System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Transport Department of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region has signed a contract
with the GIS/Trans Limited of the United States, commissioning it
to conduct a feasibility study on Hong Kong's Transport
Information System.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, the GIS/Trans Limited, an American firm
specializing in transport geographic information system, will act
as an advisor to the department on the up-to-date technology on
data warehousing, data query and communication protocols, which is
required for the Transport Information System.
</P>
<P>
"The study will focus on the means to collect, process and
disseminate both static and dynamic traffic and transport
information in Hong Kong," said a spokesman for the department
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Such information includes routes, fares and schedules of the
public transport, traffic volume as well as real time traffic
conditions," added the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"To make the system an efficient and user-friendly one, we also
need information about traffic diversions, traffic forecasts and
statistics on traffic accidents," he said.
</P>
<P>
The study, which is expected to be completed early next year,
will also explore the opportunities for private sector
participation in the development and management of the system and
the areas for priority application. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
