<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Retail Sales Rise in 2nd Quarter of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua)-- Hong Kong has witnessed a
strong rebound in retail sales in the second quarter this year,
according to a report released Tuesday by the Census and
Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
The report showed that the value of total retail sales in June
1999 was estimated at 14.9 billion HK dollars (1.9 billion U.S.
dollars), six percent lower when compared with that in June 1998,
but after discounting price changes, there was virtually no change
in volume terms over a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Sales of food, alcoholic drinks and tobacco and of
miscellaneous consumer goods picked up further, to increases of
four percent and six percent in volume, and sales of consumer
durable goods other than motor vehicles had a significant growth
of 11 percent in volume, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The performance of retail business improved further in overall
terms in June, underpinned by the pick-up in local consumer demand
as economic conditions turned better, and the sustained revival in
inbound tourism also contributed, according to a government
secretariat spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The significant growth in sales of consumer durables other than
motor vehicles reflects an increased spending on home appliances
and furniture, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
