<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French, German Foreign Ministers Visit Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine and his German counterpart Joschka Fischer began a 24-hour
visit to Kosovo Tuesday morning to urge all groups in Kosovo to
abandon any form of violence, said French Foreign Ministry
officials.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine and Fischer will meet with the U.N. civil administrator
in Kosovo, Bernard Kouchner, and the commander of the U.N. Kosovo
Peacekeeping Force (KFOR) Michael Jackson.
</P>
<P>
They will also meet with the chief of Kosovo Liberation Army (
KLA) Hashim Thaci, the Kosovo Albanian moderate leader Ibrahim
Rugova, the chief of the Serb Orthodox Church Monseigneur Artemije,
and the leader of the Movement of Serb Resistence Momcilo
Trajkovic.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers will also visit the headquarters of
French and German troops serving in KFOR in Kosovska Mitrovica and
Prizren, located in north and south Kosovo respectively.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Radio-Television Luxembourg on Tuesday,
Vedrine said that the U.N. is far from completing its peacekeeping
task in Kosovo and that he will tell the KLA that it must disarm
itself completely.
</P>
<P>
"I will tell them, and especially Mr. Thaci, that we expect the
KLA to transform truely into a political force and not to be a
fighting force any more," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
