<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Meets Papua New Guinean Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan met here today with Evoa Lalatute, special envoy of the
Papua New Guinean prime minister and secretary of the Department
of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Lalatute is here for the seventh consultation between foreign
affairs departments in the two countries, which was held from
August 23 to 24, sources from the Chinese foreign ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Yang Jiechi and Lalatute presided
over the event, during which they engaged in in-depth exchange of
views on bilateral relations and regional and international issues
of common concern, and reached ranging consensus.
</P>
<P>
Lalatute, on behalf of the Papua New Guinean government,
reaffirmed its adherence to the one China policy, and it
recognizes that Taiwan is an inalienable part of the Chinese
territory, and that it does not develop official ties with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side expressed appreciation for that. 
</P>
</TEXT>
