<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HSBC Launches One Billion HK Dollars Three-Year Issue for WB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong and Shanghai
Banking Corporation (HSBC) announced Tuesday that it launched a
benchmark three-year fixed-rate issue of one billion HK dollars (
128 million U.S. dollars) for the World Bank last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The deal, which represents one of the largest public
transactions in Hong Kong dollars by a supranational borrower in
1999, has helped establish a large, liquid benchmark for the Hong
Kong dollar market.
</P>
<P>
The issue, which was in the form of a 7.75 percent note, due on
September 13, 2002, executed under the Global Debt Issuance
Facility, was widely distributed among asset managers and
financial institutions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
