<HEADLINE> HK Airport Returning to Normal Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Operations at the Hong Kong
International Airport were gradually returning to normal following
Sunday's accident involving a China Airlines MD-11 aircraft, the
Airport Authority said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Billy Lam, chief executive officer of the Airport Authority,
said airlines had agreed where possible to provide larger aircraft
and more flights to help ease congestion at the airport, and that
the backlog of flights was expected to be cleared within the next
two days.
</P>
<P>
Lam said the Airport Authority had asked various airlines to
deploy more staff and flights to help these stranded passengers.
</P>
<P>
The Airport Authority would continue to provide whatever
assistance airlines needed to better serve passengers, he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
