<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi share market Tuesday
witnessed profit-selling by local financial institutions in blue
chips, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The 100-index of Karachi Stock Exchange closed down by 1.31
percent, or 16.86 points, to 1267.46 with a trading volume of 241
million shares.
</P>
<P>
Domestic financial institutions which had been silent for a few
days Tuesday resorted to heavy profit-selling in blue chip stocks,
said a stock dealer.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 209 traded scrips, share prices of 60 securities
recorded gains, 89 sustained losses while prices of 60 chips
remained unchanged. 
</P>
