<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shell OIl Company to Resume Operations in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Shell Petroleum Development
Company is to resume operations in its northern swamp field of
Nigeria's Niger-Delta area.
</P>
<P>
In a new release issued Monday in Warri, Delta State, the local
Ijaws community told Shell and other sister companies operating in
the area to commence work following a settlement agreement
reached between the government and Shell company.
</P>
<P>
The Ijaws of Warri have agreed to let the world major oil
company into the oil field after 211 days of closure, The Post
Express reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The stoppage of operations followed a 2,000 barrels oil spill
at Odidi, which Shell blamed for sabotage of local people, while
the local community maintained that it was a result of equipment
failure occasioned by old pipelines in the area.
</P>
<P>
The Delta State government had appealed to the communities to
let oil companies resume operations, saying that the stoppage of
operations had been affecting government revenue.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Shell and other companies are asked to
look into the issue of compensation to the affected people while
the local communities are required to embark on a public
enlightenment campaign to their people so that nobody will
henceforth disrupt operation on account of the oil spill again.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture had suffered a loss of about 2.5 billion
U.S. dollars following a shut in by the militant Ijaw youths who
stopped oil operations in the area since January 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Ministry to Be Formed to Link Education, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Iran is to set up a new ministry
to replace the existing Higher Education Ministry in an effort to
forge closer link between academic research and industrial
development.
</P>
<P>
Higher Education Minister, Mostafa Moin, said on Tuesday this
idea, contained in the ministry's draft as part of the third Five
Year Development Plan (2000-2005), has been approved by cabinet
ministers.
</P>
<P>
The new ministry will be called Ministry of Sciences and
Technology or Ministry of Research Sciences and Technology, he
said. This will be a drastic move in reform since the 1979 victory
of Islamic Revolution.
</P>
<P>
A bill on the new establishment will be presented to the
government and Majlis (parliament) six months after the
development plan is approved.
</P>
<P>
Iran boasts of its education and fundamental research, but it
feels difficult to translate those advantages into new industrial
productivity. In the new structure, efforts will be made to
"eliminate the legal and executive gaps existing in the current
structure," Moin added.
</P>
<P>
The development plan for the next five years envisages closer
ties between universities and industrial and executive
organizations. Such links, Moin said, are to contribute to the
country's independence in the areas of economy, politics, science
and culture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
