<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Chinese Premier Meets ROK Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhu spoke highly of the cooperation between China and ROK in
all fields since the two countries forged diplomatic ties seven
years ago. The development of 21st century-oriented cooperative
partnership between China and ROK is in the fundamental interests
of the two peoples and is conducive to regional peace, stability
and development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Cho commended the achievements made by China during the past
five decades after the founding of New China. He told Zhu his
mission on the current China tour is to exchange views with the
Chinese on state-to-state and army-to-army relations and issues of
common interest, with the goal of further enhancing the mutual
understanding and friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Cho extended greetings from ROK President Kim Dae-Jung and
Prime Minister Kim Jong-Pil to Zhu, who in turn asked Cho to
convey his regards to Kim Dae-Jung and Kim Jong-Pil.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian and Xiong Guangkai, deputy
chief of the General Staff of the People's Liberation Army, were
among those present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Cho is the first ROK defense minister to visit China since the
two countries forged diplomatic ties in 1992.  
</P>
</TEXT>
