<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania to Introduce Doping Controls in First Division </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Professional Soccer League (LPF) said in a statement on
Tuesday it would pick two players each from eight teams and test
them before games. "The controls will start this weekend," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Stefan Vrabioru, 23, died after collapsing in his first
division debut last month. He was the first Romanian soccer player
involved in a doping case.
</P>
<P>
Although he had tested positive with methandienone, doctors
said that the anabolic steroid could not have caused Vrabioru's
death and the cause might be an untreated heart condition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
