<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Chinese Premier Meets Mozambican Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
today that the Chinese government values its ties with Mozambique
and the Chinese are willing to elevate the bilateral friendship
and cooperation to a new level.
</P>
<P>
The premier made the remark at his meeting with visiting
Mozambican Defense Minister Aguiar Real Mazula and his party here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the friendship between China and Mozambique goes
back for many years, and that bilateral cooperation has flourished
in political, economic, military and cultural arenas since the
establishment of diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed the guests on China's views on the
international situation, China's domestic situation, and its
principled stance on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Mazula extended gratitude from the Mozambican people to China
for the support and assistance given by the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the Taiwan issue, Mazula said that Mozambique
steadfastly adhered to the "one China" position.
</P>
<P>
Mazula and his party arrived here on August 21 for an 11-day
official goodwill visit as guests of Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian.  
</P>
</TEXT>
