<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Slightly Lower in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed slightly
lower on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday erasing earlier gains
after facing resistance at the 2,150 level.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) went down 3.95 points
to end at 2,120.02 in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 563.09 million shares valued at 729.81
million Singapore dollars (433.93 million U.S. dollars). Losers
outnumbered gainers by 284 to 48 with 111 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Gen Int topped the volume list with a turnover of 75.59 million
units. AFP was the second most heavily traded stock with 64.68
million shares done. GoldenAg was the next with 43.57 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Seaview led gainers of the day rising 70 cents to close at
11.00 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem gained 30 cents to finish at
15.80 Singapore dollars. SPH picked up 20 cents to end at 29.00
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, OCBC headed the descent of the day incurring a
loss of 20 cents to close at 11.20 Singapore dollars. HL Hin F
lost 10 cents to finish at 3.62 Singapore dollars. Nera Tel
retreated 9 cents to end at 1.95 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the stocks closed lower amid some profit-taking
and caution ahead of the U.S. Fed's rate-setting Federal Open
Market Committee meeting later in the day.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that a 25 basis point rise in the Fed funds rate
has already been factored into the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
