<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Mauritian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
here today that the Chinese government and its people cherish the
traditional Sino-Mauritian friendship and would like to push
forward the existing bilateral friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
"China and Mauritius have carried out sincere cooperation in
various fields since the two countries forged diplomatic relations
27 years ago," Zhu said at a meeting with Deputy Prime Minister
and Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Trade Rajkeswur
Purryag of Mauritius.
</P>
<P>
Zhu especially expressed his appreciation for the rapid
development of trade and economic relations between the two
countries, saying that there is great potential and great
expectation for the two sides to conduct cooperation in various
forms and through different channels.
</P>
<P>
"China would like to join Mauritius to explore new ways of
economic cooperation," he added.
</P>
<P>
Purryag said that Mauritius is opening to the outside world in
terms of economic development and warmly welcomes Chinese
businesses to introduce investment into the country.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China's support has an important bearing on
the economic development of his country.
</P>
<P>
Purryag arrived here Monday afternoon to start a five-day
official visit to China as guest of Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
