<HEADLINE> Airport Closure, Rainstorms Strand Passengers in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A large number of passengers
have been stranded at the Hong Kong international airport due to
the airport closure and rainstorms.
</P>
<P>
By 2:30 p.m. Tuesday, the airport had announced the
cancellation of 24 flights, including 15 departures, while some
176 flights were delayed.
</P>
<P>
The Airport authority has contacted major airlines to make fast
arrangements for the stranded passengers to get on board, and
offer them the latest flight information.
</P>
<P>
Cathay Pacific said it will operate close to 80 percent of its
normal schedule Tuesday as part of a progressive recovery of
operations.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong airport closed Sunday evening after a China
Airlines jet land-crashed at 6:45 p.m. It resumed operation at 1:
00 Monday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
