<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Rise 0.44 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 60.21
points, or 0.44 percent, to close at 13,633.87 Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover stood at 4,349 million HK dollars (557
million U.S. dollars), 291 million HK dollars (37 million U.S.
dollars) more than the 4,058 million HK dollars (520 million U.S.
dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Counter, Utilities and Properties all gained
slightly, increasing 0.44 percent, 0.64 percent and 0.84 percent
respectively. The Commerce and Industry lost 0.11 percent.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended higher with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index up 2.14 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corporations Index up 1.47 percent.
</P>
<P>
The stock market was closed Tuesday morning due to bad weather.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index went up 156.98, or 1.16 percent, to open at
13,730.64 in the afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
