<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Chief of General Staff Meets ROK Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the General
Staff of Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), today met with
visiting Republic of Korea (ROK) National Defense Minister Cho
Sung-Tae and declared that the military relations between China
and ROK have enjoyed a steady and healthy development.
</P>
<P>
Fu, also a member of the Central Military Commission, voiced
his belief that the current visit by Cho, on the 7th anniversary
of the forging of diplomatic ties between the two countries, will
surely promote the growth of friendly ties between them and their
respective armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Over the issue of Taiwan, Fu said that one of the missions of
the PLA is to safeguard the sovereignty and territorial integrity
of China. "The PLA is ready at any moment to smash any
conspiracies to split China," reiterated Fu, adding, "We will
continue to hold to the stand of 'One Country, Two Systems' and
peaceful reunification, but we are absolutely not committed to
abandoning the use of force."
</P>
<P>
Cho Sung-Tae expressed his satisfaction over the incessant
development of military relations between the two countries,
adding that the ROK will work with China to contribute to the
growth of such army relations and to peace and stability in the
region and the world at large. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UPU Emphasizes Potential of Direct Mail Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Direct mail will become a major
factor in postal business to offset the impact of competition from
electronic communications, Director General of the International
Bureau of the Universal Postal Union (UPU) Thomas Leavey said here
today.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at the first World Conference on Direct
Mail which was part of the on-going 22nd Universal Postal Congress
(UPC) in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Direct mail is an important methods of communications between
businesses and consumers and mail advertisements are just one kind
of direct mail. As postal services around the world are suffering
loss of business volume due to the competition of electronic
alternatives, the volume and revenue of direct mail has been
growing steadily in recent years.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, direct mail generated nearly 430 billion U.S. dollars
worth of sales revenue and created more than 24 million jobs in
the United States alone.
</P>
<P>
Leavey said that direct mail is the biggest potential growth
area in the postal market and that its growth will not only
promote postal services per se, but also increase the volume and
revenues of a wide range of industries, including advertising,
printing, data bases, distribution, retail and manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
"There is a whole industry out there that stands to benefit,"
he said, adding that postal organizations should strengthen
cooperation with related industries in the direct mail market.
</P>
<P>
The World Conference on Direct Mail has brought together
representatives from postal administrations, operators and
business partners. It will develop a Direct Mail Market
Development Program in order to build a strong partnership between
postal enterprises and strategic partners.
</P>
<P>
An official from China's State Postal Bureau (SPB) said at the
conference that direct mail service in the country is less
developed than in some other countries. Direct mail accounts for
only 20 percent of the total volume of China's mail services which
account for 11 percent of the country's postal revenue.
</P>
<P>
He noted that spending on advertisements through direct mail
was a negligible part of the total sales of the country's
advertising industry.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that the rapid economic growth of China has
provided much room for the development of direct mail market. By
the year 2005, direct mail will become the fifth greatest means of
advertising in China, following radio, TV, press and out door
advertisements, he said.
</P>
<P>
The SPB has already set up the China Postal Advertising Company.
Meanwhile, postal administrations in 24 provinces in the country
have also set up direct mail companies. All capital cities of
provinces in the country will set up a direct mail production
center in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The SPB official said that China will target two groups of
customers in developing direct mail services. One is large
enterprise groups, and the other is Chinese and international
brand and postal sales companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
