<HEADLINE> Canada Pledges Sierra Leone Three Million Dollars in Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Canada has pledged 4.5 million
Canadian dollars (about 3 million U.S. dollars) in support of the
on-going peace process in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The Ottawa Citizen newspaper reported Tuesday that Canadian
Foreign Minister Lloyd Axworthy made the pledge Monday during his
meeting with visiting Sierra Leonean Foreign Minister Sama Banya.
</P>
<P>
Banya briefed Canadian officials on the state of the three-
month-old peace accord between government forces and the
Revolutionary United Front, the report said.
</P>
<P>
More than eight years of civil war in the tiny west African
republic has claimed 150,000 lives and displaced one million
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
