<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall in Tokyo on Weak Financial Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed lower in Tokyo
Tuesday, with financial issues falling due to profit-taking
following their recent sharp gains.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 138.14 points, or 0.76
percent, from Monday's close to end at 18,095.41.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all First
Section issues, dropped 11.65 points or 0.77 percent to 1,507.07.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 940.74 million
shares from 965.63 million shares Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fuji Bank was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
The banking industry, Monday's best performer, ended up the
biggest loser, falling 4.65 percent, followed by insurance firms
and brokerage houses.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, export-oriented high-tech issues moved up, helped by
Monday's surge on Wall Street and the U.S. dollar's upturn against
the yen, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 623 to 560, with 136 issues ending unchanged. 
