<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0216 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Internet Commerce Procurement Application Market to Explode </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The worldwide Internet
commerce procurement applications market, now still in its infancy,
will explode in the next few years, according to a report released
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report from the U.S. research firm International Data
Corporation (IDC) said that the market reached 147 million U.S.
dollars in 1998 and blistering growth will drive revenues to 5.3
billion dollars as soon as 2003.
</P>
<P>
The IDC estimates the number of users of the applications will
increase from 600,000 in 1999 to 250 million by 2003.
</P>
<P>
According to the IDC, Visio, a Seattle-based software vendor,
started using a Web-based procurement system only a year ago, and
its processing cost has already plummeted from 113 dollars per
purchase order to just six dollars.
</P>
<P>
After surveying the top 40 Internet commerce procurement
vendors and more than 75 end-user organizations that have
implemented their products, the IDC concluded that worldwide
businesses running these Web-based procurement applications are
projected to generate savings of up to 103 billion dollars on
transitions totaling 1.375 trillion dollars by 2003. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
