<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Bishkek for Five-Nation Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BISHKEK, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here this afternoon for a five-nation summit with leaders
of Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was accorded a red carpet welcome at the airport by
Kyrgyz President Askar Akayev.
</P>
<P>
The Bishkek summit scheduled for Wednesday will be the fourth
of its kind since 1996 when the heads of state of the five nations
met in Shanghai, China.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, the leaders of the five nations will sign a
joint statement on regional security and economic cooperation, a
Chinese Foreign Ministry official told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the five nations are expected to stress the set-
up of a multi-level dialogue, consultation and cooperation on
regional security and explore ways to enhance economic cooperation
among them.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day stay in Bishkek, Jiang is also expected to
sign with Kyrgyz President Akayev an additional border agreement,
which will settle the remaining disputes over the last piece of
territory between the two countries, thus clearing all obstacles
in further enhancing bilateral relations, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage include Vice Premier Qian Qichen, Minister in
charge of the State Development Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan,
Director of the Policy Research Office of the CPC Central
Committee Teng Wensheng, Vice Foreign Minister Wang Yingfan,
Deputy Director of the General Office of the CPC Central Committee
You Xigui, and Director of Jiang's Office Jia Ting'an. 
