<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan Shilling Declines Against Other Currencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan shilling has lost
ground significantly against the major currencies due to changes
at the international market and a slight rise in demand for
foreign exchange at the local market.
</P>
<P>
Compared to last week's trading, the shilling turned weaker
Monday, in some instances weakening with more than one shilling
against the sterling pound, the Daily Nation newspaper reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The shilling lost 14 cents against the U.S. dollar to stand at
74.49 shillings Monday from 74.35 shillings last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Against the British pound, it shed 1.23 shillings to stand at
120.46 shillings from last Thursday's closing of 119.30 shillings.
As a result, the shilling has breached the mark of 120 shillings,
the first such breach to the pound in a long time.
</P>
<P>
Market watchers said that there was no link between the decline
of the shilling and the change of the minister in Kenya's Ministry
of Finance.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts noted that there was no cause for alarm, saying
the fall of the shilling was associated with cross-currency
changes at the international market and a slight rise in demand
for foreign exchange at the local market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
