<HEADLINE> UNHCR Official Interested in Rwanda's Efforts for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A United Nations official has
said that he was very much interested in reconciliation and the
effort of the Rwandan government to have all its refugees back and
reintegrated, the Rwanda News Agency (RNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Albert Alain Peters, director of Africa Bureau of the United
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), who arrived in
Kigali Monday on a three-day working visit to Rwanda, said his
current tour of Rwanda is "a follow-up to Commissioner Sadako
Ogata's visit this June", RNA has learnt from the UNHCR office in
the Rwandan capital.
</P>
<P>
He said that ever since the genocide ended in Rwanda, the
repatriation of refugees has been a major achievement of the
government, together with the international community.
</P>
<P>
"Rwanda alongside with Kosovo and Bosnia has enjoyed quite a
substantial portion of the UNHCR's assistance all over the world,"
Peters was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Peters will tour various activities
implemented by the UNHCR in Rwanda, Gihembe camp, housing
Congolese refugees, and meet several officers of the European
Union community.
</P>
<P>
He will proceed to Geneva in Switzerland and also visit
Ethiopia, Kenya, South Africa and Cote d'Ivoire. 
</P>
