<HEADLINE> Thorpe Breaks 200m Freestyle World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Australian sensation Ian Thorpe
broke his own world record in the men's 200 meters freestyle on
Tuesday at the Pan Pacific championships in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Thorpe set a new world best of one minute 46.00 seconds in the
final, beating the previous record of 1:46.34, which he set in the
semifinals on Monday. 
