<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Turns out World's Largest Moon Cake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- An 11-sq-m moon cake, believed
to be the biggest confection of its kind on Earth, was recently
concocted in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The moon cake, now on display at the ongoing '99 Shanghai Mid-
Autumn Moon Cake Festival, has been confirmed by the Shanghai
Office of the Guinness Book of World Records.
</P>
<P>
The cake, made by the Shanghai Xinqiao Food Co., Ltd., is 3.67
m in diameter and weighs 5,474 kg.
</P>
<P>
Ingredients included 1,200 kg of flour, 3,500 kg of lotus-seed
paste, 500 kg of sugar, 30 kg of oil and 25 kg of eggs.
</P>
<P>
Carved on top of the cake are 26 dragons, signifying the
reunification of the Chinese nationalities.
</P>
<P>
Eating and trading moon cakes is a tradition during China's Mid-
Autumn Festival, which falls on the 15th day of the eighth month
of the lunar calendar. This year's Mid-Autumn Festival is
September 24.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
