<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Panda Has Two Cubs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A giant panda in Beijing Zoo
gave birth to two cubs on Monday only a week after a giant panda
in southwest Sichuan province had triplets.
</P>
<P>
Known as "Yong Yong" the 18 year old has previously given birth
to nine cubs, including three sets of twins.
</P>
<P>
Panda breeders say that the first cub was born at 5:00 pm and
the second at 8:00 pm yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Because a giant panda can only suckle one cub during her
lactation, the breeders and zoo keepers have to feed the cubs with
milk by turns.
</P>
<P>
"Yong Yong" is actually considered to be quite old even though
a panda's life expectancy is usually 36 years. Zoo keepers,
therefore, took great care of her when she was pregnant. Now she
is in good health.
</P>
<P>
The giant panda is an endangered species with only 1,000 living
in the wild in China.
</P>
<P>
So far, 58 pandas have been born in Beijing zoo which currently
has 19 pandas in captivity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
