<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills One, Injures 13 in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Severe damages of four
squatter huts in the New Territories of Hong Kong Monday by a rush
of water and debris resulted in one fatality and 13 injuries,
according to the Civil Engineering Department Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
By 10:00 a.m. Tuesday, the Goetechnical Engineering Office's (
GEO) Emergency Control Center of the Civil Engineering Department
received 66 reports of landslides.
</P>
<P>
John Massey, acting head of the GEO, said a team of landslide
investigation specialists has already been dispatched to
investigate the cause of the incident.
</P>
<P>
As a safety precaution, about 20 families living in nearby
squatter huts were evacuated.
</P>
<P>
At 12:00, the Hong Kong Observatory canceled the red rainstorm
warning signal, which replaced the black rainstorm warning signal
at 10:00 a.m. Landslide warning was also canceled in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The banks, courts, clinics and stock market that were closed in
the morning due to bad weather reopened in the afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
