<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception Marks Sino-Brazilian Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a reception
here today to mark the 25th anniversary of the establishment of
Sino-Brazilian diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siwei, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), was among those present at the
reception.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said at the occasion that the two
countries have enjoyed fruitful cooperation in political, economic,
cultural, educational areas since the forging of diplomatic ties
25 years ago, and bilateral ties have developed in an all-round
and smooth manner.
</P>
<P>
He also noted the fact that China and Brazil established a
strategic partnership in 1993, saying that these two important,
developing countries are economically complementary, thus there
exists enormous potential and broad prospect for bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Qi expressed the conviction that through joint efforts, a
comprehensive and cooperative relationship between the two
countries will continue to grow in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian ambassador to China Affonso Celso de Ouro-Preto said
at the occasion that there is a solid foundation for the growth of
bilateral ties, and confirmed that the two countries have not only
cooperated in political and trade aspects, but have also a number
of proposals for safeguarding a just and peaceful international
order.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sino-Brazilian cooperation in the space sector has
served as a good model for cooperation between developing
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
