<HEADLINE> Widest Dry Dock Under Construction In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 24 (Xinhua) -- China is building its widest dry
dock at a shipyard in Yantai, a coastal city in east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the dock, which is 120 meters wide, 400
meters long and 14 meters deep, started in August, 1997 and is
expected to be completed at the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The dock will be equipped with three cranes with a total
handling capacity of 2,400 tons.
</P>
<P>
It will be used to build large vessels and container ships as
well as freighters.  
</P>
