<HEADLINE> World Sexology Congress Being Held In Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 600 doctors,
psychiatrists, educators and social workers from across the world
are discussing sexology at a five-day congress in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The 14th World Congress on Sexology is being held in the Hong
Kong Convention and Exhibition Center from August 23 to 27.
</P>
<P>
"I am delighted that Hong Kong has been chosen to host this
prestigious international congress," said Betty Tung, the wife of
the Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
at the opening ceremony of the congress on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The congress would provide participants with an excellent
opportunity to exchange ideas and to embrace new challenges for
sexology in the new millennium, she said.
</P>
<P>
The congress, sponsored by the World Association for Sexology,
was founded in 1978 and convenes every two years.
</P>
<P>
"Particularly meaningful is that this is the first world
sexology congress on China's soil and the last of this millennium,
" said Emil M. L. Ng, president of the organizing committee of the
congress.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jieping, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress of China, who is the founder of the
Chinese Sexology Association and the honorary president of the
Chinese Medical Association also delivered a speech on the history
of sexology in China.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu, sexology was first developed in China as early
as 2000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The congress was hosted by the Hong Kong Sex Education
Association and the Department of Psychiatry with the University
of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
