<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe To Open Prison System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Efforts by the Zimbabwe Prison
Services (ZPS) to introduce the open prison system are at an
advanced stage, the daily Herald reported here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Prison Services spokesman Oliver Chigariro as
saying that some officers were sent to Denmark, which is
sponsoring the whole project, to understudy existing projects in
that country.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to reduce the number of inmates in the
country's prisons to manageable levels, and will start at
Connemara Prison near Gweru of central Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
 Zimbabwe's prisons hold about 20,000 prisoners, 4,000 more
than their carrying capacity. The prison service is looking at
ways of reducing the number of prisoners in the country's jails
following the success of the community service program.
</P>
<P>
"The community service scheme has had a success rate of over 90
percent," Chigariro said.
</P>
<P>
The number of prisoners was increasing because of the
prevailing economic conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
