<HEADLINE> 5 Pro-Israeli Militiamen Wounded in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Five members of the pro-Israeli
South Lebanon Army (SLA) were wounded Monday evening in south
Lebanon during attacks by Lebanese guerrillas, Lebanese security
sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The five militiamen were wounded when Hezbollah guerrillas
fired three mortar rounds at the SLA outpost at Braachit in the
western sector of the Israeli occupied border zone in south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israeli warplanes responded an hour later with a raid on the
wadis between Zibqine and Jabal Botom that is opposite
Braachit. No casualties were reported.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has since been
spearheading a guerrilla war to oust the Israeli occupation troops
and their allied SLA out of the country. 
</P>
