<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0530 GMT, August 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI -- The UN Environment Program (UNEP is promoting the
concept of a "life cycle" economy, said UNEP Executive Director
Klaus Toepfer here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Life cycle thinking implies that everyone in the whole chain
of a product's life-cycle from the cradle to the grave has a
responsibility and a role to play, taking into account all the
relevant external effects," he said. (UNEP-Life Cycle-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- An agreement on licensing the imports and exports of
ozone-depleting substances is expected to enter into force, the U.
N. Environment Program (UNEP) said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
By August 12, twenty countries and regions had approved the
Montreal Amendment to the Montreal Protocol on Substances that
Deplete the Ozone Layer, which met the precondition of at least 20
ratifications for the pact to be effective in November 10 this
year. (UNEP-Ozone-Agreement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- General Motors of Canada Ltd.Monday announced
investment of 20 million Canadian dollars (about 13 million U.S.
dollars) in a new research and development site in Oshawa, Ontario,
according to a CTV report.
</P>
<P>
Later in the day, Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien
expressed welcome to the GM's announcement, which came months
after it laid off 500 workers, CTV said. (Canada-General Motors-
Investment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) said on
Monday that the developments of Brazilian economy in the first
half of this year were significantly better than expected, but
urged the government to accelerate structural reforms to lay
foundations for sustained recovery.
</P>
<P>
"Developments in the Brazilian economy during the first half of
1999 have been, on the whole, significantly better than expected
under the revised IMF-supported program that was approved by the
executive board at the end of March 1999," the IMF said in an
annual review of the Brazilian economy. (IMF-Brazil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Foreign direct investment entering Mexico during
the first half of 1999 amounted to 5.468 billion dollars,
according to the Trade and Industrial Promotion Secretariat and
the Bank of Mexico Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the period, 78 percent of foreign direct investment went to
the manufacturing industry, thus greatly supporting job creation.
(Mexico- Foreign Direct Investment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- Peru's fish product exports rose to 1.077 million
metric tons during the first seven months of this year, up by 238
percent the volume placed abroad during the same period of 1998,
Fishing Ministry reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fish meal sold on the international market registered a total
of 898,000 metric tons, while fish oil exports amounted to 123,000
tons. (Peru-Fish Exports)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- The Chilean economy shrank 2.9 percent in the first
half of this year compared with the same period in 1998, the
central bank reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the country's Gross Domestic Product GDP)
has fallen to the lowest level since the crisis in 1982,
attributing the drop to the decline of internal demand and the
Asian economic crisis. (Chile-Economy) 
