<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Has its Eye on 2020 Rubber Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 24 (Xinhua) -- With a projected growing
demand of the natural rubber in the future, Cambodia strives to
revive its rubber industry from now on.
</P>
<P>
Some local industry analysts said earlier that rubber's global
production next year was estimated at 6.6 million tons, while
demand expected at 17 million tons. And in 2020, the production
would be 7.3 million tons against the demand of 28.5 million tons.
</P>
<P>
These figures show that the natural rubber is returning to the
world stage, after being overtaken by synthetic which was
developed during the World War two to overcome rubber supply
disruption from Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia is undertaking a multimillion dollar plan in Kompong
Cham to develop rubber small holdings with the funding of a French
Development Agency.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, families will be given plots of land to plant
and tend rubber seedlings, and they will be provided with subsidy
until the trees are ready for bleeding latex, which will be bought
by a corporation to be established.
</P>
<P>
The French will also help Cambodia develop a national rubber
research institute to help improve the quality of latex and to
establish a standard for Cambodian rubber to meet buyer's needs.
</P>
<P>
The institute will help Cambodia develop better planting,
tapping and processing techniques to improve the current poor
quality of latex production in the country.
</P>
<P>
The plan will have good prospects of reaping profits from a
long-term point of view, said experts here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0311 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
