<HEADLINE> NATO-destroyed Yugoslav Oil Refinery Resumes Partial Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- An oil refinery at Novi Sad of
Yugoslavia, destroyed during NATO's 78-day bombing, resumed
partial production on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The refinery, about 60 kilometers north of Belgrade, with a
daily capacity of 300 tons of diesel oil and 850 tons of heavy oil,
will have refined 500,000 tons of the two products by the end of
the year, according to its manager.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 destructive bombs were dropped on the refinery
during NATO's bombing against Yugoslavia earlier this year.
</P>
