<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgrade Protests Against France for Destroying TV Transmitter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavian Foreign Ministry on
Monday lodged a strong protest with the French government for
destroying a Serb television transmitter in northern Kosovo by the
French troops in the NATO-led peacekeeping forces in Kosovo (KFOR).
</P>
<P>
The protest was handed over to the charge d'affaires of
Switzerland's embassy in Yugoslavia, who represented France
because Belgrade broke off diplomatic relations with it on March
25 after NATO began air raid on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
This conduct is illegal and hard to understand, which brutally
trampled on the sovereignty of Yugoslavia and Serbia, a statement
released by Yugoslavia Foreign Ministry said later.
</P>
<P>
The statement urged the French troops of KFOR to restore the
transmitter as soon as possible so that people in Kosovo and
southern Serbia could receive TV and radio signals from Belgrade
again, and demanded the French government to compensate Radio-
Televizija Srbija for the damage.
</P>
<P>
The transmitter on Mount Mokra Gora, near the town of Zubin
Potok, was demolished by the French on August 16 after surviving
more than 10 attacks during NATO's 78-day bombing earlier this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
