<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Import Drops by 4.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar imported 762 million U.S.
dollars worth of commodities in the first four months of this
year, reducing by 4.2 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest data published by the country's Central
Statistical Organization, of the total import value, capital goods
amounted to 393 million dollars or 51.57 percent, consumer goods
297 million dollars or 38.97 percent and intermediate goods 72
million dollars or 9.46 percent.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar mainly imports from 11 countries and one region --
China, Japan, Singapore, Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia, India,
Hong Kong, the United States, Britain, France and Germany.
</P>
<P>
According to the data, Myanmar's foreign trade, including the
border trade, totaled 1.162 billion dollars in the first four
months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
