<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0323 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Export Up 9.3 percent in 1st 4 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar exported 399 million U.S.
dollars' worth of goods in the first four months of this year,
showing an increase of 9.3 percent over the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures published by the country's
Central Statistical Organization, of the total export value, the
private sector accounted for 290 million dollars or 72.68 percent,
while the government sector 109 million dollars or 27.32 percent.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar mainly exports agricultural and marine products and
timber.
</P>
<P>
To boost exports, Myanmar introduced some encouraging measures
such as giving special privileges to exporters who fetch 2 million
dollars from export earnings or above, simplification of export
formalities and addition of border trade points.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the government is also planning to expand the range of
export goods, add non-traditional commodities such as natural gas
in its export items and increase the export quota of processed and
manufactured goods to enable its export goods value-added.
</P>
<P>
According to the official statistics, Myanmar's foreign trade,
including the border trade, totaled 1.162 billion dollars in the
first four-month period of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
