<HEADLINE> China's July Interbank Trading Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Turnover on China's interbank
money market topped 73.74 billion yuan in July, up 37.8 percent
from the previous month.
</P>
<P>
This included 31.64 billion yuan in credit, 42 billion yuan in
bond repurchase agreements, and 100 million yuan in spot bonds.
</P>
<P>
Trading was most active on 20-day, 30-day and 60-day items,
accounting for 34.2 percent, 25.6 percent and 31.6 percent of all
transactions, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The weighted average interbank lending rate and repurchasing
rate in July were 2.85 percent and 2.67 percent, down 0.5 percent
and 0.4 percent, respectively, from June.  
</P>
</TEXT>
