<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tropical Rainstorm Sweeps Over HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Tropical rainstorm still
lingering over Hong Kong has forced the closure of all the banks,
courts and stock market Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Observatory issued the black rainstorm warning
signal Tuesday morning, and advised local residents to stay at
home for possible flooding and landslide.
</P>
<P>
By 8:00 Tuesday morning, a total of 67 flooding cases and 61
landslide incidents were reported. Some road sections were closed.
</P>
<P>
The Home Affairs Department of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region opened some 21 temporary shelters for the
people in need of accommodation.
</P>
<P>
Motorists are required to reduce speed and extend the distance
between themselves and the vehicle in front.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Hospital Authority announced the closure of its
specialist clinics, general out-patient clinics, geriatric day
hospitals and psychiatric day hospitals. Accident and Emergency
services at hospitals will remain normal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
