<HEADLINE> Interbank Forex Trading Hits 3.17 Billion U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- China's interbank foreign
exchange trading for July amounted to 3.17 billion U.S. dollars,
according to the latest statistics released by the Shanghai-based
China Foreign Exchange Trade System.
</P>
<P>
This figure included 3.09 billion U.S. dollars, 293 million
Hong Kong dollars, and 5.13 billion Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The weighted average exchange rate of the U.S. dollar
fluctuated slightly, with the U.S. currency closing at 8.2774 yuan
by the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong dollar ended the month at 1.0658 yuan, while the
Japanese yen was trading at 7.1703 yuan per 100 yen at the end of
July.  
