<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Storm Leaves Two Dead in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The recent flooding that is
occurring following heavy rainfalls in Venezuela have left at
least two dead and 10,000 homeless, authorities said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The deaths occurred Sunday night when two persons were hit by
falling high-tension cables in Vargas State, next to Caracas.
</P>
<P>
About 8,000 persons lost their homes in Anzoategui State, the
vicinity most affected by the storm, in northeast Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
Civil Defense authorities are housing victims in temporary
quarters.
</P>
<P>
Around 30,000 people were cut off by the floods, while the
storm destroyed crops and bridges and caused landslides on
highways.
</P>
<P>
The government has declared a state of emergency due to the
rainfall and flooding in Anzoategui, Aragua, Bolivar, Delta-
Amacuro, Vargas and Zulia states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
