<HEADLINE> Peru's Fish Exports Increase Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 23 (Xinhua)-- Peru's fish product exports rose to
1.077 million metric tons during the first seven months of this
year, up by 238 percent the volume placed abroad during the same
period of 1998, Fishing Ministry reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fish meal sold on the international market registered a total
of 898,000 metric tons, while fish oil exports amounted to 123,000
tons.
</P>
<P>
Peru is one of the few top fish meal producers and exporters in
the world. 
</P>
