<HEADLINE> Factfile on World Women's Discus Champion Dietzsch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Following is the factfile on
German Franka Dietzsch who won the women's discus title on the
third day of the world championships on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Born: January 22, 1968.
</P>
<P>
Second in the 1986 world junior championships, fourth in the
1989 World Student Games then 12th in the 1992 Barcelona Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Was eighth in the 1993 Stuttgart world championships and
improved to fourth at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Enjoyed her best season to date last year when she finished
first in the Budapest European championships and also took gold in
the Johannesburg World Cup. 
</P>
