<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Lauds China's Achievements in 5 Decades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Yasser Arafat, chairman of the
Palestinian National Authority, said that facts have testified
that the Chinese people chose a suitable political system which
has led to the enhancement of their country's prestige in the
world.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with Xinhua, the chairman said that
reality has shown the political road the Chinese people took five
decades ago suits their geographic environment, cultural identity
and historic civilization. As a result, the Chinese people have
made great progress in national construction and are progressing
along the path of scientific and technological development.
</P>
<P>
This year the People's Republic of China celebrates its 50th
founding anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Praising the great strides made by New China in economic reform
and construction over the past 50 years, Arafat spoke highly in
particular of the achievement made over the past 20 years when
the opening-up and reform program is being carried out.
</P>
<P>
He said he views with admiration and appreciation these
accomplishments that are embodied in China's steady economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
They also contributed to China's enhanced standing in the world
community, enabling the country to assume a constructive and
important role both in Asia and the world at large, he added.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who has visited China for more than a dozen times since
the mid-1960s and has been an old friend of Chinese leaders of
three generations, said the economic policy pursued by China has
taken into consideration the political and economic changes in the
outside world. China's success story in the economic field has
encouraged other nations and peoples in their efforts for
attaining economic and political liberation.
</P>
<P>
Talking of China's foreign policy, he said the diplomatic
principle of peaceful coexistence as pursued by China is in total
conformity with the objectives and principles sought by the United
Nations. China has all along supported international efforts aimed
at maintaining world peace and security. And at all international
forums, particularly at the United Nations, it has taken side with
peoples struggling for their rights to self-determination, freedom,
independence and security on their own soil.
</P>
<P>
He said these policies have earned the country respect from all
third world countries. "We highly praise China for its friendly,
uncompromising and firm stand in supporting the struggle of our
Palestinian people ever since the very beginning and at all
international platforms," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking about Sino-Palestinian relations, Arafat said, "We
highly value the close friendship that bonds us with China for
many years. These ties have further expanded and deepened
throughout four decades."
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinian people have always viewed China with deep
respect and admiration and will never forget the support China
has given them," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We need China's support and cooperation, particularly during
the present decisive phase when the Palestinian people are on the
threshold of achieving their freedom and independence on their
soil." He said he is sure that China will, as always, stand on the
side of the Palestinian people in establishing an independent
state with Jerusalem as its capital.
</P>
<P>
On China's resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong,
Arafat said the Palestinian people joined all freedom- and peace-
loving peoples of the world in welcoming the historic event.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that as China has adopted a wise and
responsible policy in dealing with the issue of Hong Kong's return,
it will undoubtedly succeed in resolving the issue of Macao's
return and in reunifying with Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0350 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former NBA Guard Michael Adams Joins IBL as Asistant Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Michael Adams, an 11-year NBA
veteran guard, has joined the International Basketball Leauge.
</P>
<P>
The Richmond Rhythm today named Adams an assistant coach. He
becomes the third NBA alumnus to become a member of the franchise,
joining team president and executive general manager Ralph Sampson
and coach Allan Bristow.
</P>
<P>
"Michael is a great asset to the Rhythm," Sampson said. "We've
added a terrific person and role model who has come through the
ranks in his playing career. Our younger players will especailly
benefit from Michael's NBA and developmental league experience."
</P>
<P>
Adams played for Sacramento (1985), Washington (1986-87, 1991-
94), Denver (1987-91) and Charlotte (1994-96) and averaged 15.0
points and 6.6 assits in his career. He was an All-Star in 1992.
</P>
</TEXT>
