<DOCNO> XIE19990824.0357 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile's Economy Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean economy shrank 2.9
percent in the first half of this year compared with the same
period in 1998, the central bank reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the country's Gross Domestic Product (GDP)
has fallen to the lowest level since the crisis in 1982,
attributing the drop to the decline of internal demand and the
Asian economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of 1999, Chile's industry decreased 3.2
percent, fishing 1.3 percent and agriculture 0.4 percent, while
the mining sector, an exception, increased 15.3 percent, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The recession has caused a 13.5 percent decrease in internal
consumption and a 14.6 percent reduction of capital, the bank said.
</P>
</TEXT>
