<HEADLINE> Bomb Explodes at Colombian Consulate in Caracas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 23 (Xinhua)-- An explosive device went off
Monday at Colombia's consulate in this capital with no one injured,
local sources said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to Colombia's General Consul in Venezuela, Jose
Alfredo Maestre, no one was hurt. However, there were damages at
the main door and windows.
</P>
<P>
Maestre described the happening as "regretful" and denied the
attack as affecting relations between Venezuela and Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place at around 3:30 local time and up to
now, no group has claimed responsibility. 
