<HEADLINE> Factfile on Women's Long Jump Winner Montalvo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Following is the factfile on
Niurka Montalvo of Spain who won the women's long jump title on
the third day of the world championships on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Born: June 4, 1968.
</P>
<P>
Married a Spaniard in February 1998 and became a Spanish
citizen in May this year.
</P>
<P>
Holds both Spanish (7.06) and Cuban (6.89) long jump records.
Jumped 6.93 in 1998 when she was effectively stateless.
</P>
<P>
Won gold in Seville with last jump and claimed silver at the
1995 world championships, going from seventh to second on her
final effort. 
