<HEADLINE> Liverpool Recovers for Victory over Leeds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Liverpool recovered from two
straight English premier league defeats to win 2-1 at Leeds on
Monday courtesy of an own goal from home skipper Lucas Radebe.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Gerard Houllier's side had been under pressure as two
1-0 defeats, by Watford last week and Middlesbrough on Saturday,
left them struggling in 17th place on the league table.
</P>
<P>
The home side went ahead after 20 minutes as a Michael Bridges
shot cannoned into the net off Liverpool's Cameroonian Rigobert
Song's left ankle.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool levelled the score through a Titi Camara goal in the
dying minutes of the first half and after 55 minutes, the second
own goal of the night came as Radebe deflected a Liverpool
freekick past Nigel Martyn to hand the guests the much-needed
victory.
</P>
<P>
The win moved Liverpool to ninth in the table. 
</P>
</TEXT>
