<HEADLINE> Factfile on World Steeplechase Champion Koskei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Following is the factfile on
Christopher Koskei of Kenya who won the 3,000 meters steeplechase
title on the third day of the world championships on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Born: August 14, 1974.
</P>
<P>
Fastest junior in the world in 1993 and only man to beat the
then world champion Moses Kiptanui over the steeplechase in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Won the world junior steeplechase title that year.
</P>
<P>
Involved in controversy in this year's Zurich Golden League
meeting when his fellow-Kenyan Bernard Barmasai, the world record
holder, said he had asked Koskei to deliberately hang back and let
him win. Koskei denied the allegation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
