<HEADLINE> Chile to Name British Doctor for Pinochet Medical Examination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, August 23 (Xinhua)-- The Chilean government will
assign a British doctor to examine the state of health of life-
long Senator Augusto Pinochet, Chilean Foreign Minister Juan
Gabriel Valdes said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that Pinochet's medical examination will be
conducted before the extradition process begins by Britain on
September 27, at the request of a Spanish judge.
</P>
<P>
Valdes said it is up to the British government to determine the
procedure to be followed in order to cite humanitarian grounds
against Pinochet's extradition to Spain.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, 83, was arrested in Britain on October 16, 1998, at
the request of a Spanish judge who is seeking to extradite him to
Spain to face charges of human rights abuses alleged to have
occurred during his rule from 1973 to 1990.
</P>
<P>
Chile has protested his detention, arguing other countries
should not be allowed to judge crimes committed on Chilean soil.
</P>
<P>
An earlier report said Pinochet would undergo medical tests
this week which would be used by defense lawyers to support their
case for his release. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
