<HEADLINE> Kipketer Appeals for Blood Testing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Men's 800m world record holder
Wilson Kipketer of Denmark called Monday on the International
Amateur Athletics Federation to catch drug cheats by imposing
blood testing.
</P>
<P>
Kipketer, a favourite to take the title for the third
consecutive times at world championships, made the comment when
the sport is facing a credit problem after several hight profile
athletes failing drugs tests recently.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Danish added that the IAAF should also take a
more consistent line in the way they tested athletes.
</P>
<P>
"I think that the athletes should be blood tested because that
is the clearest way of finding out if they are taking drugs or not,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
"I also think that the top 20 athletes in each event should be
tested all through the year and not just randomly as happens at
the moment," he added.
</P>
<P>
However, the blood testing would only be used on a voluntary
basis at the Sydney Olympic Games for reseach purpose only, as
what it was stated by the International Olympic Committee earlier
this week. 
</P>
