<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Veteran Wins Women's Discus Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEVILLE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- German veteran Franka Dietzsch
produced her first ever gold medal at world championships when she
threw 68.14 meters in her penultimate attempt to win the women's
discus event on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Dietzsch, 32, had a disappointing performance in Athens two
years ago when she failed to win anything with three no-shows.
</P>
<P>
Anastasia Kelesidou of Greece was second with a throw of 66.05m
and Nicoleta Grasu of Romania finished third with 65.35.
</P>
<P>
Competing against a strong field including World University
Games champion Grasu and 1995 world champion Ellina Zvereva of
Belarus, Dietzsch admitted that she felt nervous entering her
position.
</P>
<P>
"I felt very nervous entering the infield before the
competition began, but I was lucky enough to get a good throw out
in the first round," she said.
</P>
<P>
The European champion had virtually settled for the gold in her
first try in which she managed to throw the discus to a distance
of 66.34 meters.
</P>
<P>
In her third throw, she improved her mark to 67.60 meters.
</P>
<P>
However, after Kelesidou had 66.05 meters in the penultimate
round, Dietzsch felt that the Greek might throw even farther in
the final round, which may well overtake her mark of 67.60 meters.
</P>
<P>
"After the Greek threw 66 meters, I knew my earlier result
might not be enough for gold. However, I was able to collect my
throughts again and calm myself which made it possible to throw so
far in the fifth round," she said.
</P>
<P>
The result and the victory may well satisfy the German, who
said that she only hoped for a brzone medal before the competition.
</P>
<P>
"I came here as the second best in the world so far this year
and I thought I would be satisfied even if I only got the bronze,"
she added.
</P>
<P>
However, Beatrice Faumuina, who won the first ever world
champion for New Zealand when she won the discus event in Athens,
would not be happy today.
</P>
<P>
Faumuina only managed 64.62 meters in her best throw to finish
in the fifth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
