<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Names New Leader for U.N. Mission in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 23 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan has decided to appoint Tom Koenigs of Germany as a
deputy special representative for the United Nations Interim
Administrative Mission in Kosovo (UNMIK), a U.N. statement said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Koenigs, who will be in charge of civil administration in
UNMIK, will replace Dominique Vian of France, who "will be
returning to his duties with the French Government," said the
statement issued by the U.N. spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary-General would like to express his gratitude to
the French Government for making available the outgoing deputy
special representative, Vian, at such short notice at the very
outset of the mission," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Annan "wishes to express his deep appreciation to Mr. Vian for
the excellent work he has done in leading the civil administration
pillar of UNMIK under very difficult and challenging
circumstances," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Koenigs was the treasurer of the City of Frankfurt between 1993
and 1997 for the city's billion deutschmark budget. Since 1989, he
has been the head of the Environmental Protection Department of
the City of Frankfurt and is responsible for environmental
protection, sewage management, the fire department and energy
supply.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
